All structure template as follows:
    the total description of the entrance or main of lib (for example: the description of the __init__.py):
        Python version:  (must)
            ***

        Role:  (if None write None)
            ***

        Lib and Version:  (if None write None)
            package - version
            (colorama - 0.0.1)

        Only accessed by:  (must)
            All / ***(the specific file)

        Modify:  (must)
            2026.3.4
            ...

    the description of sub-lib (for example: the description of the color_define.py):
        Python version: ***  (must)

        Lib and Version:  (if None write None)
            package - version
            (colorama - 0.4.6)

        Only accessed by:  (must)
            __init__.py, colorful_print.py

        Modify:  (must)
            2026.3.4
            ...

    the description of function:
        all parameters should be described clearly, and the parameter of **kwargs and *args should also be described clearly.
        the clear formal parameters:
            all parameters should be described clearly. you should describe it's type, input formation,etc.

        the *args and **kwargs:
            the constraints of the input of *args and **kwargs should be described clearly.
